From 57a7e7169a194dc8ce37dccfa5aa00fc6ff435f8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 20:21:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] Refine canonical API: extractor control flow, frozen
 vocabulary, simplified roadmap

Incorporates the second review round:

- Canonical Extractor Control Flow (normative): value-producing extractors
  return (value, ok) with #optional_ok and write their own HTTP error before
  returning false; destination-filling extractors (web.body(ctx, &dst) ->
  bool) take a caller-owned pointer, keeping ownership and storage explicit.
  or_else statement blocks are formally banned from all documentation
- Query family frozen as query / query_int / query_int_or with explicit
  per-type names (pattern query_<type> / query_<type>_or); no generic
  typeid-based query_or in the MVP; _or default applies only on absence,
  malformed values are always 400
- web.ok and web.created contractually exact shorthands of web.json with
  fixed status; convenience responders may never diverge from the renderer
- Middleware-Produced Request Data (normative): no user_data/locals/
  map[string]any on the canonical Context; typed extraction procedures
  (current_user) are the canonical channel, gate-only middleware for routes
  that don't need the value; advanced Request_State reserved for the typed
  context; onion post-next semantics made conditional on transport
  guarantees, decided at the Phase 2 Spec Gate
- No code generator, no mandatory CLI, no heavy metaprogramming; OpenAPI
  moved out of the MVP as a future optional layer (Route_Info direction)
- Systems API renamed Advanced API (app_init + Advanced_Config)
- Roadmap simplified to: 1 minimal productive API, 2 middleware and groups,
  3 performance core (radix, arenas, limits/timeouts), 4 production,
  5 future (OpenAPI, WebSocket, streaming, HTTP/2, core:net/http adapter);
  web.app() default-policy contract delivered progressively
- Canonical vocabulary table added; docs and ai-context updated to match

